# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .gitignore for vouchfx-samples (reference samples + CI harness)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

## .NET build output (orders-dotnet, and the vendored engine checkout)
bin/
obj/

## SpecFlow's MSBuild code-behind generator writes this next to each .feature
## file (migrations/from-specflow) — regenerated on every build, never source.
*.feature.cs
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/
artifacts/
publish/
*.dll
*.exe
*.pdb
project.lock.json

## NuGet
*.nupkg
*.snupkg
.nuget/
packages/

## Python build output / caches (inventory-python)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.venv/
venv/
dist/
build/

## Java / Maven / Gradle build output (payments-java)
target/
.gradle/
*.class
*.jar
!**/lib/*.jar

## Node.js build output / caches (ledger-jsonrpc)
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
.npm

## The vendored engine checkout — fetched fresh by scripts/bootstrap.* from the
## commit pinned in ENGINE_PIN. Never committed; always reproducible.
.vouchfx-src/

## CI/local run output — JUnit XML + HTML reports written by scripts/run-sample.*
## Anchored to the repo root: a sample's own build tooling may legitimately
## use an "out" directory name at some other depth.
/out/

## Rendered GitHub Pages site — regenerated by scripts/build_site.py from
## site/ + the repository's markdown on every build/CI run. Never committed.
/_site/

## Ad hoc local build_site.py validation output (e.g. SEO/canonical spot checks
## against a non-default output dir). Never committed.
/_site_seo_check/

## Test results & coverage
[Tt]est[Rr]esult*/
*.trx
*.coverage
coverage*.json
coverage*.xml
TestResults/

## IDEs
.vs/
.idea/
*.user
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

## Local secrets & environment
*.secrets
secrets.json
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

## OS / temp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
*.tmp
*.swp
*~

## Agent / tooling scratch
.claude/
.serena/
